{
  "texts": [
    "Generative adversarial networks (GANs) refer to the class of generative models that generate synthetic data by learning through probability distributions of real data (Goodfellow et al. 2014).",
    "GANs are designed with generator and discriminator models.",
    "The generator produces realistic-looking synthetic data while taking random vectors as inputs.",
    "The discriminator's task is to classify real data from generated (synthetic) data.",
    "GANs use an objective function as a joint loss function with minimax optimization."
  ]
}